	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It sounds like you may have damaged the sprite hardware. Goonies II and SMB both use Sprite 0 (afaik) to do screen splits for their status bars. Given how that method of screen splitting usually requires the program to wait in a loop until the detection happens, it'd make sense that both games would hang.
<br />
<br />SMB3's lack of sprites just backs this up.
<br />
<br />Makes me wonder what, exactly, got damaged though, since there are a few reasons why sprites would fail.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


